snippet.textDisplay: @kurtTraver totally agree, the world was a little more light-hearted and glossy than the way we're used to seeing it. I have another complaint to add to that, and I think it's very related, and it's that the music itself made the game feel more silly too. Older DK games had a mysterious, gloomy, ominous feeling, which was half the art direction and half Wise's music. We're missing both halves here, and while I liked the gameplay in this one, I wasn't too happy with the overly upbeat score.
snippet.textOriginal: @kurtTraver totally agree, the world was a little more light-hearted and glossy than the way we're used to seeing it.
